<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-14T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-14T17:00:00-05:00" n="322" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d322">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/4949: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister Resident in Ethiopia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-14T18:00:00-04:00">August 14, 1936—6
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>338. Department’s 337, August 13, 5 p.m. A further telegram from the
                                Paris Embassy states that the French Foreign Office has suggested
                                that you take up with the Italian high command the question of
                                avoiding any difficulty regarding the importation of the shipment
                                into Ethiopia.</p>
                            <p>If any objections are raised by the Italian authorities please
                                report.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>